<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01 · Rotisserie oven service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Commercial rotisseries are heavy-duty mechanical equipment. Different service tree than convection ovens.</h2>

    <p>Rotisserie ovens are specialty equipment for chicken specialists, deli rotisserie programs, ethnic restaurants (Mexican, Middle Eastern, Caribbean), and high-volume catering. The dominant brands in LA: <strong>Hardt</strong> (Canadian, Inferno and Sabre series), <strong>BKI</strong> (DR-34 series), <strong>Henny Penny</strong> (rotisserie line), and <strong>Hickory Industries</strong>. Premium tier ($15,000 to $40,000 new). Built to run 8 to 16 hours per day continuously with chickens or meats on rotating spits.</p>

    <p>The service tree is distinct from convection ovens. Mechanical drive components (motor, chain, sprockets) take the heavy wear. Drip pan and drain handling matters more than on convection because grease accumulates fast. Glass doors thermal-stress crack at 6 to 10 years from rapid cooldowns when doors open during service. Igniter and thermocouple service on gas models. None of this is exotic, but it requires brand-specific knowledge to diagnose efficiently.</p>

    <p>We service rotisseries across all five SoCal counties. <strong>$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair.</strong> BHGS Licensed #A49573. EPA 608 Universal certified (#1346255700410). BBB A+ accredited.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 COMMON FAILURES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">02 · Common rotisserie failures</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What we diagnose most often.</h2>

    <ol class="failure-list">
      <li><strong>Drive motor for rotating spits.</strong> Heavy-duty wear from continuous operation. Hardt and BKI motors typically year 8 to 12 service life. Replacement $480 to $780.</li>
      <li><strong>Drive chain plus sprockets.</strong> Chain stretches and sprocket teeth wear. Always replace as a paired set, mismatched chain on worn sprockets fails again in months. Year 5 to 7 typical on heavy-use chicken specialists. $260 to $480 paired set.</li>
      <li><strong>Drip pan drain blockage.</strong> Grease buildup in drain line causes overflow into the cabinet floor and electrical compartments. Clean and treat the drain line as part of preventive service. $180 to $320 cleaning.</li>
      <li><strong>Heating element (electric models).</strong> Element open-circuits at year 8 to 12 standard wear. $480 to $780 replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Igniter plus thermocouple (gas models).</strong> Gas rotisseries (Hardt, BKI gas, Henny Penny gas) use spark or hot-surface igniter with thermocouple gas valve safety. Both wear together. Replace as paired set. $260 to $440.</li>
      <li><strong>Door gasket compression.</strong> High temperature plus frequent door opening compresses gasket. Year 4 to 6 replacement typical. $260 to $420.</li>
      <li><strong>Glass door cracking.</strong> Thermal stress at 6 to 10 years. Replace with manufacturer-spec borosilicate (not aftermarket soda-lime). $400 to $720 with gasket.</li>
      <li><strong>Thermostat and temperature controller.</strong> Standard wear and calibration drift. $260 to $420 replacement plus calibration.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 REAL REPAIR STORIES -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">03 · Recent rotisserie repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Composite stories from the route.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Four rotisserie jobs from the past 90 days. Names omitted; the technical scenarios are typical of what we see weekly.</p>

    <div class="story-grid">
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Chicken restaurant chain in Hollywood · Hardt Inferno 3500, 9 years old</h3>
        <p>Drive motor making grinding noise plus reduced spit rotation speed. Diagnosed: drive motor bearings end-of-life, classic 9-year heavy-use failure. Replaced motor with OEM Hardt part. Tested 4 full rotation cycles before leaving. Total: $120 + $680 motor + $180 labor = $980.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Deli in Pasadena · BKI DR-34, 6 years old</h3>
        <p>Spit rotation intermittent, jumps and skips. Diagnosed: drive chain stretched plus drive sprocket teeth worn. Replaced chain and sprockets as paired set per standard practice. Tested rotation cycles. Total: $120 + $360 paired set + $80 labor = $560.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Mexican restaurant in East LA · Henny Penny rotisserie, 8 years old</h3>
        <p>Won't ignite reliably. Diagnosed: spark igniter electrode pitted plus thermocouple weak (reading low millivolts on gas valve). Replaced igniter and thermocouple as paired set. Total: $120 + $260 igniter + $120 thermocouple + $40 labor = $540. Customer set on annual maintenance after seeing the cascading-failure pattern.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Specialty butcher in Beverly Hills · Hardt Sabre, 11 years old</h3>
        <p>Door glass cracked from corner. Diagnosed: thermal stress crack typical at 11 years on older soda-lime glass spec. Replaced door glass with manufacturer-spec borosilicate replacement plus refreshed door gasket while accessing the door assembly. Total: $120 + $480 glass + $120 gasket = $720.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 HONEST SCOPE -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">04 · Honest scope</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What we service, what we don't.</h2>

    <p><strong>We service:</strong> Hardt (Inferno and Sabre series), BKI (DR-34 series), Henny Penny rotisserie line, Hickory Industries rotisseries. Gas and electric. Commercial countertop and floor-mount configurations. Drive motor, drive chain and sprockets, igniter and thermocouple, heating element, drip pan and drain service, door gasket, glass door replacement, thermostat.</p>

    <p><strong>We don't do:</strong></p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li>New rotisserie installation (specialty installer trade with gas line and ventilation work)</li>
      <li>Custom hood and vent modifications (HVAC trade)</li>
      <li>Vertical broiler / shawarma machine repair (different specialty equipment, similar visual category but different service tree)</li>
      <li>Smokehouse rotisseries (smoke-generation systems are different trade)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 05 PRICING -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">05 · Pricing</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Rotisserie repair costs in Southern California.</h2>

