        <tr><td>Door gasket</td><td>$320 to $480</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Glass door replacement (with gasket)</td><td>$480 to $720</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Thermostat / temperature controller</td><td>$320 to $480</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Annual maintenance contract</td><td>$280 to $440 per visit</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Multi-component repair</td><td>$1,200 to $2,400</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Warranty</td><td>90 days parts plus labor</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 06 BRANDS WE SERVICE -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">06 · Brands</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Rotisserie brands we service.</h2>

    <ul class="brand-list">
      <li><strong>Hardt</strong> (independent, Canadian). Inferno series (3000, 3500) and Sabre series. Premium tier. Heavy-duty drive motors and chain systems. Dominant in LA chicken specialists and high-volume rotisserie operations.</li>
      <li><strong>BKI</strong> (Standex Food Service). DR-34 series the most common. Mid-premium tier. Strong delicatessen install base in LA. <a href="/brands/bki-rotisserie-repair/">BKI rotisserie repair brand page</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Henny Penny</strong> (independent, Ohio family company). Rotisserie line plus broader food-service equipment. Common in mid-tier and chain restaurant rotisserie programs.</li>
      <li><strong>Hickory Industries</strong> (independent). Smaller install base in LA but fully supported, parts via Hickory authorized distribution.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 07 WHY US -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">07 · Why operators call us</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Six reasons.</h2>

    <ul class="why-list">
      <li><strong>Drive motor and chain expertise.</strong> Mechanical drive components are the heaviest-wear items on rotisseries. Brand-specific motor and chain knowledge required.</li>
      <li><strong>Glass door spec awareness.</strong> Manufacturer-spec borosilicate replacement, not aftermarket soda-lime that fails again in months.</li>
      <li><strong>Drip pan drain treatment.</strong> Grease buildup is the silent failure mode. We treat drains as part of preventive service.</li>
      <li><strong>BHGS Licensed #A49573 plus EPA 608 Universal certified (#1346255700410).</strong> See our <a href="/credentials/licensed/">licensing page</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>$120 commercial diagnostic, no after-hours surcharge.</strong> Phones answered 24/7.</li>
      <li><strong>Annual maintenance contracts.</strong> High-volume chicken specialists especially benefit from predictable maintenance.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Sister sub-services: <a href="/commercial/oven-repair/combi-oven-repair/">combi oven repair</a>, <a href="/commercial/oven-repair/convection-oven-repair/">convection oven repair</a>. Parent: <a href="/commercial/oven-repair/">commercial oven repair pillar</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 08 FAQ -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">08 · FAQ</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Rotisserie repair, common questions.</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      {faqs.map(f => (
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>{f.q}</summary>
          <p set:html={f.a} />
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 09 BOTTOM CTA -->
<section class="bottom-cta">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Rotisserie down? Call us 24/7.</h2>
    <p>Hardt, BKI, Henny Penny specialists. Drive motor and chain experts. BHGS Licensed #A49573. $120 commercial diagnostic.</p>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <a href={phoneHref} class="btn-primary">☎ Call {phone}</a>
      <a href="/contact/" class="btn-secondary">Book Online</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</Layout>

<style>
